import React from 'react'
import Link from 'gatsby-link'

const SecondPage = () => (
  <React.Fragment>
    <h3>User Experience Design</h3>

    <p>User experience design is a broad discipline of research. A UX designer
    plans a study for <span className="bold">user research</span>,
    conducts the study, analyzes the data, and uses the results to inform their
    designs. Deliverables from these studies can include <span className="bold">personas</span>, <span className="bold">journey maps</span>, and <span className="bold">design requirements</span>.</p>

    <p>After this research come the <span className="bold">wireframes</span> and <span className="bold">prototypes</span> that
    most people associate with UX design. UX designers use journey maps to identify what their users need,
    identify pain points and bottlenecks, and try to <span className="bold">help users attain their goals</span> with the product
    while <span className="bold">meeting the client's goals</span>.</p>

    <p>UX designers then <span className="bold">test these designs with users</span>, validating
    their layouts and designs with people. Designers take feedback from users to
    revise their designs in an iterative process.</p>

    <p>If my description seems a little all over the place, UX designers often
    have to wear multiple hats. Some are also project managers, developers,
    market researchers, copy writers, etc.</p>

    <h3>Front-End Development</h3>

    <p>While web development used to refer to code on the back-end - typically
    server side code like PHP, ASP, Ruby - a front-end developer writes the
    interactive elements of a site or app. Frameworks like React and libraries
    like jQuery are common tools, in addition to vanilla Javascript.</p>

    <p>With new tools constantly releasing, front-end developers often build
    large web apps with complex logic. As such, simply being able to code
    isn't enough; front-end devs are problem solvers, and they need
    disciplined processes and methodologies like kanban and scrum to keep their
    projects on track.</p>

    <p>A good developer also tests their code, documents it, and comments their
    code, and stays consistent with the rest of the project.</p>
  </React.Fragment>
)

export default SecondPage



